comments.body:
These dissertations were in the correct collection ([Near Eastern Studies](https://dataspace.princeton.edu/handle/88435/dsp01b8515n39n)) but for some reason, this collection has submitters and reviewers groups configured in DataSpace for it, see below:
![Screenshot 2023-10-27 at 10 49 08 AM](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/7795797/4c55cfac-3a63-4fb1-b3bb-03915bd4f7be)

Groups in the "Accept/Reject/Edit Metadata" group are defined as follows:
![Screenshot 2023-10-27 at 10 50 19 AM](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/7795797/a6138ea6-9c2b-4522-ad57-4955b2cb8f59)

I spot-checked several other collections within dissertations, and they are all configured as follows, with no groups defined for any sort of manual intervention (which is what I believe we would expect for all collections):
![Screenshot 2023-10-27 at 10 48 58 AM](https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/assets/7795797/17f1c904-da5a-4360-8b0a-19555fc277cc)

For next steps, I'll check in with RDSS and Special Collections to see if there is a known reason for the difference between Near Eastern Studies and other dissertation collections and update here with more information.
RDSS confirmed not knowing why this collection would be different from the others.  I have a question out to Lynn and Christa now to see if they know.

tiger-data-app.title: Creating lots of projects to benchmark performance

comments.body:
With 5,000 projects but split among 5 from root namespaces (`td-demo-06..10`) and querying at the root `/`. 

```
Getting counts by data_sponsor zz001 department  took 152.62 ms 0.15 seconds
Getting counts by data_sponsor zz003 department  took 1234.47 ms 1.23 seconds
Getting counts by data_sponsor zz007 department  took 1227.51 ms 1.23 seconds
Getting counts by empty data_sponsor  and empty department  took 1819.50 ms 1.82 seconds

Getting counts by data_sponsor zz007 department THREE took 1247.46 ms 1.25 seconds
235 records for zz007 department THREE
```

Limiting by root namespace e.g. `td-demo-06` times are pretty good: 
```
MEDIAFLUX_ROOT_NS=/td-demo-06 bundle exec rake projects:query[zz007]

Getting counts by data_sponsor zz007 department  took 155.25 ms 0.16 seconds
142 records for zz007 department 
```

But querying across all namespaces times start to creep up:
```
MEDIAFLUX_ROOT_NS=/ bundle exec rake projects:query[zz007]

Getting counts by data_sponsor zz007 department  took 1386.00 ms 1.39 seconds
710 records for zz007 department 
```
